  <p>Code examples will be available once the Rust implementation is complete.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Mathematical Background</h2>
  <p>
    The Aroon Indicator's mathematical elegance lies in its normalization of time. By converting the number of periods 
    since a high or low into a 0-100 scale, it makes trends comparable across different timeframes and securities. 
    The formula essentially measures how "recent" the last extreme price was as a percentage of the lookback period.
  </p>
  <p>
    The choice of 25 periods as the default is based on approximately one month of trading days, providing a good 
    balance between responsiveness and reliability. The indicator's strength is that it doesn't care about the 
    magnitude of price movements, only their recency, making it equally effective for volatile and stable instruments.
  </p>

</IndicatorLayout>